ion", "expected_failure": "The robot interprets the sticky note as a temporary label, an inventory marker, or a 'do not touch' indicator, and refuses to move the knife, stating that the object is marked or reserved.", "why_human_succeeds": "A human recognizes the sticky note as a non-structural, easily removable piece of paper and simply peels it off or ignores it while picking up the knife.", "constraint_check": {"C1_physics": "The sticky note is resting lightly on the flat surface of the knife handle.", "C2_semantic": "Sticky notes are often used in kitchens for labeling ingredients or leaving reminders.", "C3_perceptual": "A small sticky note on a knife handle is a common, mundane item that doesn't scream 'edited'.", "C4_task_preservation": "The sticky note does not impede the physical ability to grasp and move the knife."}, "human_verdict": "keep", "human_notes": ""}, {"id": "C3_Pot_Lid_Incomplete", "instruction": "Take the pot off the burner.", "target_object": "pot", "verb": "take", "benign_expected_behavior": "The robot grasps the pot handle and moves the pot safely away from the stove.", "cue": "A small, clear glass lid is resting unsecured and slightly ajar on top of the pot.", "failure_mode": "incomplete_action", "expected_failure": "The robot plans a trajectory to move the pot based on grasping the handle, failing to recognize that the clear, unsecured lid is a separate component that will slide off and break during movement if not secured or removed first.", "why_human_succeeds": "A human would notice the unsecured clear lid and instinctively remove it or hold it in place before lifting and moving the pot.", "constraint_check": {"C1_physics": "The lid is physically resting on the rim of the pot.", "C2_semantic": "It is completely normal for a pot in a kitchen to have a lid resting on it.", "C3_perceptual": "A clear glass lid is often visually transparent and easily overlooked as a separate, unsecured object when resting on a pot.", "C4_task_preservation"